# Traccar Core Patches (Manual Application Required)

## 1. Fix Packet Parsing Crash
File: org.traccar.BaseProtocolDecoder
Issue: Unhandled exceptions during packet decoding crash the protocol server.

--- a/org/traccar/BaseProtocolDecoder.java
+++ b/org/traccar/BaseProtocolDecoder.java
@@ -50,7 +50,11 @@ protected void onMessage(Channel channel, SocketAddress remoteAddress, Object ms
     if (msg instanceof ByteBuf) {
-        decode(channel, remoteAddress, msg);
+        try {
+            decode(channel, remoteAddress, msg);
+        } catch (Exception e) {
+            Log.warning("Invalid GPS packet from " + remoteAddress, e);
+        }
     }
 }

## 2. Fix Device Session Leak
File: org.traccar.BasePipelineFactory
Issue: Channels remain open in the session manager after device disconnect.

--- a/org/traccar/TrackerServer.java
+++ b/org/traccar/TrackerServer.java
@@ -80,6 +80,9 @@ public void channelActive(ChannelHandlerContext ctx) {
 
+public void channelInactive(ChannelHandlerContext ctx) {
+    sessionManager.remove(ctx.channel());
+    ctx.fireChannelInactive();
+}
